Supporters for the cancer disease campaign attended a dinner organised by Grace Wanjiku Mweru Cancer Foundation at Home Care Center in Limuru town.Among them are GWM foundation founder Grace Wanjiku, the chairman of Kenya Network for Cancer Organisations Dr David Makumi, cancer survivors and religious leaders.Dr Makumi spoke on how to care for cancer patients. He also applauded the government for the measures it was putting in place for tackling the disease like improving service and acquiring of equipment.Present were Furaha Primary School principal Eunice Mwathi and Springs of Bethel Church Bishop John Waichere .